MANUFUTURE DASHBOARD IMPLEMENTATION PLAN (from manufuture-rms-v12.html)
Last updated: 2026-04-21

Source prototype
- File: `manufuture-rms-v12.html`
- Nature: standalone HTML + CSS + JS with dummy datasets + Chart.js.
- What to extract: menu structure (modules), page layouts, widgets, tables, modals, and user actions.

Current Laravel integration status (already in repo)
- Vendor portal routes (protected by `manufuture.portal` middleware):
  - `/vendor-panel/mf` dashboard
  - `/vendor-panel/mf/orders`
  - `/vendor-panel/mf/products`
  - `/vendor-panel/mf/pos` (coming-soon)
- Admin portal routes:
  - `/admin/mf` dashboard
  - `/admin/mf/orders`, `/admin/mf/products`, `/admin/mf/pos`, `/admin/mf/returns`, `/admin/mf/helpcenter`, `/admin/mf/omnichannel`, `/admin/mf/aipulse`
- Layouts + views:
  - `resources/views/layouts/vendor/manufuture.blade.php`
  - `resources/views/vendor-views/mf/*`
  - `resources/views/layouts/admin/manufuture.blade.php`
  - `resources/views/admin-views/mf/*`
- Portal separation:
  - `stores.portal` = `vendor` | `manufuture`
  - Manufuture login redirects to mf dashboard.

============================================================
ALIGNMENT RULES (KEEP WITH EXISTING 6MART SYSTEM)
============================================================
Non-negotiables
- Reuse existing 6Mart data + flows wherever possible:
  - Orders: existing orders + order details/updates/filters
  - Products/Items: existing item/product management (store-scoped)
  - POS: existing POS screens and endpoints
  - Returns: existing return/refund/return request flows (if present)
  - Store/Vendor auth: existing vendor guard + store scoping
- Avoid new DB tables unless absolutely required for MVP.
- For each prototype menu item we decide one of:
  - REUSE: map to an existing 6Mart module/route/controller/view
  - WRAP: create a thin MF wrapper page that calls existing queries/endpoints but uses MF layout
  - COMING SOON: show the page but keep it static until a real backend exists

What “MF Dashboard” means in our project
- It is NOT a separate application.
- It is a different portal UI for the SAME store/vendor data, chosen by `stores.portal='manufuture'`.

============================================================
BUSINESS LOGIC (YOUR MODEL) — ADMIN MANAGES BOTH SIDES
============================================================
Actors
- Super Admin / Admin (Platform operator):
  - Controls onboarding, permissions, packages, and operational rules.
  - Has visibility across ALL Manufuture suppliers and Vendor shops.
- Manufuture (Supplier / Producer):
  - Produces products and sells to Vendor shops (B2B).
  - Needs supplier dashboard: incoming purchase orders, inventory, dispatch, invoices.
- Vendor Store / Shop (Retailer):
  - Sells to end customers (B2C) using existing 6Mart marketplace + delivery flows.
  - Needs retail dashboard: customer orders, item management, POS, marketing.

How they interact (high-level)
1) Supplier publishes/maintains a catalog (supplier-side).
2) Vendor shops can “source” items from suppliers (vendor-side).
3) Vendor sells items to customers (existing 6Mart order flow).
4) Admin monitors everything and can resolve disputes, enforce rules, and manage payments/settlements.

Important: current technical implementation reality (today)
- We currently separate portals using `stores.portal`:
  - `vendor` = retailer shop portal
  - `manufuture` = supplier portal UI
- BUT both currently still operate on the same underlying store model and standard 6Mart tables.
- True supplier→vendor B2B purchasing requires additional domain models (see “Future (new tables)” below).

Operational responsibility (admin/super admin)
- Onboarding:
  - Approve Manufuture supplier stores
  - Approve/deny Vendor stores
  - Convert store portal type vendor ↔ manufuture
- Catalog governance:
  - Control which supplier products can be listed by vendors
  - Control pricing rules / commissions / subscriptions
- Order governance:
  - Monitor supplier POs + vendor customer orders
  - Handle returns/disputes/escalations
- Finance governance:
  - Track settlements/payouts (existing wallet/payout where possible)
  - Future: supplier invoices + vendor payables (needs new models)

MVP interpretation (aligned with existing 6Mart)
- Phase 1 MVP will focus on:
  - Manufuture portal UI + analytics for the supplier’s own store data (KPIs, products, orders)
  - Admin control panels to manage portal types and package visibility
- Supplier→Vendor “B2B purchase orders” will be planned but marked Coming Soon until approved.

Decision (confirmed)
- We start with MVP using existing 6Mart data for Manufuture dashboards.
- No new tables for supplier→vendor purchasing in this phase.

