============================================================
2) PROTOTYPE DATASETS + WHAT THEY MEAN
============================================================
============================================================
1.1) MODULE → EXISTING 6MART MAPPING (REUSE / WRAP / COMING SOON)
============================================================
Vendor Manufuture portal (store-scoped)
- Dashboard (dashboard): WRAP
  - Render MF UI but compute KPIs from existing orders/items data.
- Orders (orders): REUSE/WRAP
  - Use existing vendor order listing + details logic; MF page can be a themed wrapper.
- Products (products/allproducts/inhouse/sellerproducts): REUSE/WRAP
  - Use existing vendor products/items listing and filters, but in MF layout.
- POS (pos): REUSE (theme only)
  - Use existing vendor POS page, swap layout to MF layout.
- Returns & RMA (returns): REUSE if return module exists; else COMING SOON.

Admin Manufuture portal (global)
- Dashboard: WRAP
  - Use existing admin analytics queries but show MF UI.
- Orders/Products/Returns/Helpcenter: REUSE/WRAP (admin scope).

Prototype modules that are NOT in core 6Mart (initially)
- Omnichannel: COMING SOON (unless order source/channel is stored in DB)
- AI Pulse: COMING SOON → MVP later using heuristics from existing data
- Supply Chain / B2B / AR / Credit line: COMING SOON (needs new domain models)
- CRM/Loyalty/Clienteling: COMING SOON (needs segmentation + points rules)
- Workforce/Tasks/Compliance: COMING SOON (needs task/audit tables)
- Vendor promotions/sponsored ads: COMING SOON (depends on marketing modules in your build)

Note on prototype “Sellers/Vendors” section
- In prototype it looks like a marketplace operator portal.
- In our MF vendor portal, those pages are usually not relevant for a single supplier store.
- Keep them admin-only or coming soon.

Dummy JS arrays in prototype:
- orders[]: B2B-style orders (id, buyer, city, channel, qty, amount, payment, status, eta)
- inventory[]: stock rows (sku, cat, stock, reserved, reorder, status)
- replenishment[]: demand forecast suggestions (suggested qty, confidence, urgency, cost)
- campaigns[], segments[]: marketing + buyer segment analytics
- clients[], loyaltyMembers[]: CRM + loyalty tiers
- listings[], keywords[]: SEO/listing health
- tickets[]: support tickets + SLA
- tasks[], complianceList[], workforce[]: ops workflows
- pulseInsights{}: AI Pulse insights buckets (inventory, revenue, crm, marketing, ops, risk)
- helpCategories[]: help center categories + article titles

These datasets define the minimum DB/API endpoints we must implement per module.

Existing 6Mart data we can reuse immediately (no new tables)
- Orders + order items: derive the prototype orders table + status badges + amount totals.
- Items/products: derive inventory-style list using existing item stock/availability fields.
- POS: reuse existing POS flows; only adjust layout/theme for MF.
- Returns/RMA: reuse if returns/refunds exist; otherwise keep "Coming Soon".

Anything that needs new domain models stays "Coming Soon" for now
- Credit line, AR aging/ledger, B2B pricing tiers, loyalty tiers/points, tasks/compliance/workforce, help center KB.


============================================================
3) IMPLEMENTATION STRATEGY (REALISTIC, PHASED)
============================================================
Principle
- Keep the UI/UX inspired by prototype, but implement with Laravel + DB.
- Do NOT port the entire prototype at once.
- Start with core pages that map directly to existing 6Mart data: Orders, Products/Items, Stock, basic KPIs.
- Keep the rest as "Coming Soon" until backends exist.

Phase 1 — Vendor MF dashboard (REAL KPIs)
- Page: `/vendor-panel/mf` (`vendor-views/mf/dashboard.blade.php`)
- Replace placeholder KPIs with DB-backed metrics scoped to logged-in store:
  - Orders today/week/month by status
  - Total sales (paid_amount) today/month
  - Products/items count (active, out-of-stock)
  - Returns count (if returns table exists; else 0 + coming soon)
- Charts:
  - Start with 1 chart only (revenue trend) using existing orders table.
  - Add more charts later.

Phase 2 — Orders (REAL list + filters)
- Page: `/vendor-panel/mf/orders`
- Implement:
  - status filter pills
  - date range filter
  - search by order id / customer / phone
  - order details link (reuse existing vendor order details route or create MF-specific wrapper)

Phase 3 — Products/Inventory (REAL list)
- Page: `/vendor-panel/mf/products`
- Implement:
  - items list scoped to store
  - stock indicator (good/low/out)
  - quick stock update action (if supported; else read-only)

Phase 4 — AI Pulse (SAFE MVP)
- Page: `/vendor-panel/mf/aipulse` (or keep coming-soon route until ready)
- MVP:
  - show "insights" cards generated from simple heuristics (low stock, top buyers, delayed orders)
  - no OpenAI dependency initially

Phase 5 — Optional modules (coming-soon → real)
- Omnichannel: show channel breakdown if you track channel field; else coming soon
- POS: reuse existing POS pages but themed in MF layout
- Returns/RMA: wire to existing order return features if present
- Help center: static FAQ pages first; then DB-backed KB later

Phase 0 (MVP guardrail)
- If a prototype feature requires NEW tables/modules, it remains "Coming Soon" until approved.
- The MVP must stay aligned with existing 6Mart modules (orders/items/pos/returns).

============================================================
FUTURE (WHEN YOU APPROVE NEW TABLES) — TRUE SUPPLIER → VENDOR B2B
============================================================
To fully support “Manufuture sells to Vendor shops”, we typically need:
- Supplier Catalog + Vendor Sourcing
  - Link supplier products to vendor products (import/copy/price rules)
  - Supplier-specific wholesale pricing / tiers (optional)
- B2B Purchase Orders (Vendor → Supplier)
  - Separate from customer orders
  - PO statuses: requested → accepted → packed → shipped → received
- Supplier Dispatch & Invoicing
  - Invoice generation + delivery terms
- Settlements / Payables
  - Vendor owes supplier; supplier payout schedule

Admin must manage:
- Approval + limits (which vendor can buy from which supplier)
- Compliance rules (returns windows, quality disputes)
- Payment rules (credit terms, Net-30, partial payments) if you want them


============================================================
